s and letters, he adds an immediacy to this lucid and stimulating text.Key FeaturesProposes a new vocabulary for the articulation of IslamOffers original comparisons between Salafism and LefebvrismHighlights the paradoxical harmony between tradition and itjihad in IslamArticulates the yearning amongst today's Muslim and Christian traditionalists for a revival of a 'golden age' from whence, they believe, all good traditions derive  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aAuthorityxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aAuthorityxReligious aspectsxIslam. 4aIslamic Studies. 7aRELIGION / Islam / Rituals & Practice.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078046840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748630257zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748630257423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748630257/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK